-- Guaranty Trust Says World Bank's IFC Offered to Buy $30 Million of Shares
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-07-26T10:20:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/guaranty-trust-says-world-bank-s-ifc-offers-to-buy-30-million-of-shares.html

          
          
             Guaranty Trust Bank Plc, a Nigerian
bank, said it is giving “serious consideration” to an offer
from the World Bank’s International Finance Corp. to buy new
shares in the company to the value of $30 million.  
          
          


  


        